&gt;&gt;Balanz: Then please enlighten me. At 63rd level, what other solo technique is possible and viable? Against what dark blue experience yielding mobs can I regularly sustain rather than chain a pet?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=1239">forum.magecompendium.com/...php?t=1239</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
The post is from the forum you moderate in the &quot;Things to kill: Levels 61 - 65&quot; section.  The technique the level 61 poster describes works all the way through 65.<br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;Balanz: It is not required to do more damage than a water pet, and I cannot recall anyone other than you suggesting that it should.<br>
<br>
Just so we are clear. I am not suggesting that its sustained damage be greater than the water pet.  However, the burst dps of the pet on test is greater than the sustained dps of the water pet.  If you review the thread you will see several people talk about the burst damage capabilities of the pet until it runs oom.  <br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;If it dealt damage comparable to air, maybe a little higher, cast stuns, tanked worse than water, dealt less damage than water but did not require positioning, then you would have a useful caster-type fire pet, with unique attributes.<br>
<br>
Why not use an air pet if what you want is a pet that stuns and does about air pet damage?  The air pet and the fire pet would then serve virtually the same roles.  <br>
<br>
That the pet's damage was magicial in nature would really only be a factor is you could somehow prevent it from entering melee range.  The only way I could see that as happening would be if the pet were rooted, but since that was not a change on test. I consider  it more productive to discuss the potential of what actually is on test namely a pet that can provide a short term dps boost that runs oom quickly.<br>
<br>
The only problem with this scenario as someone pointed out was that if the pet is summoned at full mana then it is always in &quot;burst&quot; dps mode.  That clearly is a problem.<br>
<br>
Hence my suggestion the pet be oom on being summoned.<br>
<br>
<br>
