 Some very good arguments have been presented on both sides, but I must ask - did the mages visiting here honestly expect the wizards of this board to climb on to this Pet Wagon? Very few of the opinions generated are against Mages gaining a better pet, many will agree upgrades are warranted. I personally feel that what is being offered will in the end not help either class in the overall desire to group.<br>
<br>
 I have had emmensely satisfying relationships with Mages of my realm and I wish to continue the alliances I have been part of. I also must admit that several aspects of this upgrade go against what I - as a wizard - should and would allow to happen. Granted I have little say in what actually will be implemented in the final draft of pet abilities, but much of what is being added simply does not feel right. A good portion of me wants to say that if this does occur then wiz should recieve:<br>
1)anananaaa<br>
2)nanaaanaaa<br>
3)nanaana<br>
4)nana<br>
 ...but that really doesnt help anything either. Another portion of me wants to declare that all is cool except for:<br>
1)this<br>
2)that<br>
3)the other<br>
4)and all the above<br>
 ... which also isnt of much use.<br>
<br>
 Hellfire, many very good alternatives have been suggested. Many good options to consider and strive for have been stated. Much has been presented that will satisfy both classes and maintain the level of respect that both entities garnered for each other through the simple matter of having survived the same trials and hazards that we face in this world called Norrath.<br>
<br>
 Quite honestly, there isnt much either class can do to resolve this... it is in the hands of SOE and thier subordinate devs. I can only hope that both they, and the Mages reading here will understand some resentment could/will occur from the myriad races of wizards populating the planet(s) we share if the alterations are bestowed as currently implied on Test.<br>
<br>
note: the above is the ramblings of a gnome wizard's emotional response. It has no technical or numerical value. But I do hope that many reading the previous pages will see options are available that will still benefit the Mage without infringing on the already (SOE induced) fragile ego of the wizard.<br>
<br>
Yahtzooba Boom<br>
53 wiz of Inny.<br>
